Package com.pace.jayvee.workflow

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Sink<T>
    This is the basic interface for a sink of data.
    Source<T>
    This is the basic interface for a source of data.
    Worker
    The Worker is the core of the JayVee architecture (the "work"horse...if you will).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BlockingHeapBuffer<T>
    A blocking heap buffer is a simple FIFO buffer implementation that keeps its contents in memory (hence 'heap') and blocks when the buffer is full and the user is trying to push or when the buffer is empty and the user is trying to pop.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BlockingHeapBuffer.BufferEndedException
    An exception thrown when trying to access a buffer that someone has already called end on (and all other items have emptied out)
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    InputBuffer
    This is a marker used to indicate that a particular field or property is an input Source to a worker or system and should be controlled and settable by the system and the system builder.
    OutputBuffer
    This is a marker used to indicate that a particular field or property is an output Sink to a worker or system and should be controlled and settable by the system and the system builder.
    Stateful
    This annotation should be placed on workers that maintain some kind of internal state.
